-1.title: A Brave Pit Bull

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

-1.plot: When Dr. Jeff examines a beloved Weimaraner who has stopped eating, he makes a surprising discovery. Dr. Baier investigates the cause of a pet rabbit's mysterious fur loss. A servicewoman asks Dr. Jeff for help with her precious Pit Bull's injured leg.

1.title: One More Chance

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

1.plot: The show follows Jeff Young and his staff at Planned Pethood Plus, a reduced animal care clinic in the Rocky Mountains of Colorado. In the premiere of this series, a dog goes into cardiac arrest shortly after arriving at the clinic.

2.title: Whatever It Takes

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

2.plot: A miniature pig with an injured leg needs surgery, but it may not be able to handle anesthesia; a French bulldog has a routine dental exam that turns into a complex operation; the team ventures into the Rockies to help a couple who rescue sled dogs.

3.title: Never Give Up

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

3.plot: Ten puppies arrive with a puzzling disease; a cat with a limp needs complicated hip surgery.

4.title: Rocks and Crocs

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

4.plot: A dog may have a broken leg, but Dr. Young suspects it's a more serious condition that requires immediate surgery. Meanwhile, a veterinary technician must overcome her fear of birds; and a cat's appetite gets it in trouble.

5.title: Mile-High Mutt

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

5.plot: A stray dog needs a home once it recovers from surgery that was required after it was hit by a car in Oklahoma. Meanwhile, a golden retriever needs immediate surgical attention after swallowing a pacifier.

6.title: Street Dog

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

6.plot: A 5-month-old puppy that belongs to a homeless man has an injured paw; a dog in pain has X-rays that reveal a severe case of bladder stones.

7.title: A Full Heart

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

7.plot: A beagle is left at the clinic after it was attacked by another dog; a golden retriever has a broken leg; a technician shows a rescued kitten's owner how to feed it if it refuses to eat; a goat needs a botched operation fixed. Also: The staff visit a farming community to help with a feral cat population.

8.title: Feline Face Lift

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

8.plot: A runaway dog is brought in by animal-control officers after it got caught in a chain-link fence. Meanwhile, a dog has buckshot in its hind quarters; a large cat has a facial injury; a dog has a sore paw; and longhorn bull calves must be gelded.

9.title: Miracle Cat

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

9.plot: An overweight cat with kidney disease struggles to survive; a dog is hit by a car while its owners are out of the country.

10.title: Holiday Miracles

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

10.plot: In this special holiday episode, the staff hosts a fun run to raise money for animals in need; a dog requires emergency surgery after it's found tied to a fence; a stray Pomeranian finds a forever home.

1.title: Full Speed Ahead

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

1.plot: In the Season 3 premiere, Amy operates on a cat with a strange appetite; Jeff tries to help a dog walk again; and the team visits an animal sanctuary to treat an injured tiger.

2.title: Race Against Time

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

2.plot: Jeff operates on a dog that's rushed to the clinic after a growth on its neck ruptures. Meanwhile, a family brings in their rabbit with strange lumps on its side; and a risky procedure is performed on a pair of rescued miniature donkeys.

3.title: A Long Way from Home

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

3.plot: A dog owner drives nine hours hoping Jeff can save her pet's leg. Meanwhile, a pack of wolves are treated at a wildlife sanctuary; and Dr. Baier cares for a kitten with a deformed leg.

4.title: On the Edge

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

4.plot: Two sisters rush their dog to the clinic with a life-threatening brain injury.

5.title: Born to Run

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

5.plot: Dr. Jeff and Dr. Petra work together as they battle to save the leg of a beloved Husky.

6.title: Friends for Life

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

6.plot: Dr. Jeff battles to fix a German Shepherd's broken elbow and get him back to his worried owner, a disabled war veteran. A cat with a swollen bladder, needs difficult surgery to save its life. And Dr Baier and Jes head to an exotic bird sanctuary.

7.title: Shelter from the Storm

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

7.plot: Dr Jeff must act fast to save a bulldog after a life-threatening accident.

8.title: Picking Up the Pieces

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

8.plot: A boxer kicked in the head by a horse requires urgent surgery to repair its skull.

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

10.plot: Dr. Jeff faces surgery he has never done before on a Rottweiler with a broken shoulder.

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

11.plot: Dr. Jeff faces tricky surgery to remove a large mass from a cherished Doberman's side.

12.title: Last Hope

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

12.plot: When a beloved poodle arrives at the clinic, Dr. Jeff discovers a life-threatening condition and rushes him into surgery.

5.title: Into the Jungle

episode of.title: Dr. Jeff: Rocky Mountain Vet (TV Series 2015– )

5.plot: When a beloved black lab swallows toxic metal, Dr. Jeff races to save his life. A lost cat is found after a year and a half absence, but has a mysterious injury. And, a tiny dog has a big, life-threatening problem.

plot: Follow Dr. Jeff and his crew as they take on some the wildest cases in their animal house of a hospital.
